%N A397872 Decimal expansion of the long/short edge length ratio of a canonical (dual-uniform) heptagonal trapezohedron.
%C A397872 The heptagonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the heptagonal antiprism.
%H A397872 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397872/b397872.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A397872 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/HeptagonalTrapezohedron.html">Heptagonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397872 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Heptagonal_antitegum">Heptagonal antitegum</a>.
%H A397872 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397872 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_03">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 3</a>.
%F A397872 Equals (csc(Pi/14)^2)/4.
%F A397872 Equals the largest root of x^3 - 6*x^2 + 5*x - 1.
%e A397872 5.0489173395223053135222144070233697235963877860565...
%t A397872 First[RealDigits[Csc[Pi/14]^2/4, 10, 100]]
